observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to strengthen its management controls and ensure full implementation of its priority programs and projects that are envisioned to help achieve desirable socio-economic development and environmental outcomes of the City, and require:
The City Development Council to
Properly plan the programs and projects before inclusion in the City’s AIP. Also, prioritize development projects that are readily implementable, and during the planning stage, consider the possible problems that may be encountered in the implementation to prevent future delays;
Allocate additional funds to the projects with insufficient appropriations, and if it is not possible, consider implementing the projects by phase;
Utilized the excess funds or savings to new development programs and projects to ensure optimal utilization;
the City Engineer to
Fast track the identification of the new location/site for those projects which are to be relocated;
Resolve Right-of-Way issues to immediately commence the implementation of the projects, and to avoid future disputes;
Follow-up the Barangay Officials on the new location of the Bag-ong Lungsod Barangay Hall;
Adhere to the target dates of implementation and find mechanisms to address unexpected situations such as quarantine protocols;
The City Planning and Development Officer to follow-up the MOA with the National Housing Authority, the partner agency;
The City Cooperative Officer to follow-up the recipient POs and cause the immediate submission of the liquidation reports, and facilitate the submission of the lacking requirements for the new release of funds; and
The CENR Officer to take initiatives by formulating equivalent projects and programs that will also mobilize the community on the marine protected area development, such as online training or face-to-face but with limited participants.

We recommended and Management agreed to strengthen its monitoring controls by requiring the CDRRM Office, CADM Office, and Mayor’s Office    to :
Ensure proper coordination among the Offices concerning the receipt and distribution of Donations In-Kind;
Ensure issuance of Acknowledgment Receipts to all future receipts of donations in-kind to confirm that donations are properly recorded and accounted for;
Ensure that all future issuances of donated items are properly supported with Issuance Form for In-Kind Donations or any document/record to prove receipt by and distribution to the intended beneficiaries; and
Determine the inventory of remaining undistributed items for recording in the Registry of Donated Relief Goods for DRRM.

We recommended that Management:

       Instruct the HRMO to require the JO/COS to submit Tax Identification Number (TIN) and Annual Registration Fee (ARF) upon hiring and renewal of contracts, respectively;

       Require the City Accountant to compute, withhold and remit the respective percentage taxes of JO/COS Personnel for CY 2018, as provided in RMC 51-2018 and other pertinent laws, rules, and regulations;

      Capacitate the City Accounting Personnel, by requiring them to attend seminars and trainings related to the latest updates on Tax and BIR Rulings

