Recommendations:
Direct the City Cooperative Officer to require the recipient to immediately  liquidate the amount of ₱1.0 million and to open a separate bank account for the said amount in case it is still in its possession:
Incorporate in the Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) all the terms and provisions cited in COA Circular No. 2012-001 to ensure the protection of public funds from losses in case of failure of the recipient to complete the project and/or in case of material violation to the terms and provisions of the MOA;
Require the City Cooperative Officer to regularly inspect and monitor the status of implementation of the project and to prepare a report thereon;
Direct the City Accountant to reclassify from the expense account “Donations” the amount of ₱1.0 million to receivables account.  Henceforth, transfers of funds to non-government organizations/people’s organizations should be treated as receivables in the books of the LGU to ensure the availability of records for monitoring purposes; and
Direct the City Cooperative Officer to thoroughly evaluate the financial and physical capability of the recipient before releasing funds as seed capital to ensure that public funds are utilized for projects aimed towards the achievement of the program’s goals and objectives.

